   Mission:
   The mission of the Germplasm and Gamete Physiology Laboratory is to
   improve the genetic, reproductive and productive efficiency of
   livestock and poultry through fundamental research on germplasm, gamete
   biology and embryology. Research is designed to: improve methods for
   the short-term preservation and cryopreservation of swine and turkey
   spermatozoa; use the study of cellular, molecular and hormonal
   mechanisms to improve egg production in turkeys; improve oocyte
   developmental competence in swine; identify factors that limit
   embryonic survival and fertility in turkeys and swine and predetermine
   embryo sex in livestock; develop and improve culture and preservation
   of swine embryos; develop methods of effectively assessing sperm
   fertilizing capacity in vitro and develop and improve methods for sex
   preselection through flow cytometric separation of X and Y sperm based
   on DNA content.

